Text:
Alpha, Beta, Gamma, and Epsilon are attending their
regular Shadow Garden debriefing.

For the next report...Gamma, you're next. How have
the results been for Mitsugoshi?

Right, we have already achieved this month's sales
targets. We are using our current excess capacity
toward business expansion and are evaluating
potential locations for a new store.

I will report back as soon as there are any new
developments.

Well done, Gamma. That's good progress. Next...
Beta. Any new intel from the Midgar Newspaper
Association?

Yes. As part of my author activities, I participated
in the salons of the aristocrats and succeeded in
directly investigating those of the upper echelons.

As a result, I have obtained intel on the source of
the voter funding we have been investigating for
some time.
We suspected some connection to the Cult. Go on.

Understood. Based on my investigation, some of the
lower-ranked aristocracies have recently experienced
a surge in their assets while also becoming politically
outspoken.

Based on the intel from a Lord who I encountered
while investigating, most recent emerging voters
are funded by fortunes made as customers at a
particular casino.

While it appears to be an ordinary casino, it is a
high-class venue exclusive to aristocrats with close
ties to the royal family. Ordinary people are not
even allowed entry.

They are highly secretive regarding their operation,
making our investigation challenging. We've learned
they've some lenience in admission when accompanying
royals...but that would pose a problem for us.

An exclusive, secretive venue that serves as a hub
for those close to the royal family... It's highly
likely they hide clues leading to the Cult.

Indeed. Since we can only gather so much intel from
the outside, we believe there is no other way but to
investigate internally.

Seeing that you've brought this to my attention,
I take it you've found a way inside?

Yes, here are the details. According to our research,
there is a temporary vacancy, and they are recruiting
staff to fill it.

The job application states no prior casino experience
and only a certain level of customer service skills
are required. I am confident I can get them to hire me.

I see. It sounds like the ideal infiltration opportunity,
but how can you be certain you'll be hired?
Regarding that, allow me to fill you in.

Beta asked me for advice on concealing her identity
as Natsume, so I've prepared false documents for her.

From her experience working as staff at Mitsugoshi,
Beta already possesses more than sufficient customer
service skills. Adding the personality she's developed
as a writer to the mix, she's a shoo-in.

I see. It sounds like you've planned it all out
perfectly. Very well. Is there anything else
you'd like to add?

Oh, about the position... It's actually for a bunny
girl... I'll be going dressed like this—
Wh-What do you think?
*gasp*

I see. It a little more extreme than your usual
outfits, but it suits you.
Yes, I think it should be fine.

Whew... I thought I might as well make it look cute,
but I was worried I went overboard...

D-Don't you think it's too suggestive?! The chest
area, in particular, is quite over the top!
Wha—?! Don't frighten me like that...

Even I naturally refrain from being overly revealing
when out in public. How about covering yourself up
a little, especially that chest of yours?!

For starters, Little Miss Airhead, you flaunting your
weapons like that...is how you make enemies! Enemies!

Grr... Just because anything suits you... I-I could
pull it off as well! I... I could!

I-I don't know what you're so worked up about,
but this is a bunny suit. It's a uniform worn at
casinos.

Sure about that? You said yourself you made it to
your taste. I think you're trying to turn Master Sha—

The door to the room opens, cutting off Epsilon's
words.

I'm back. What's with all the commotion? Something
happen?

Welcome back, Zeta. We were discussing my next
mission.

Oh, sorry for interrupting... Hey, is that you, Beta?
Why're you wearing a bunny suit?
Are you trying to be a therianthrope? Heheh.

C'mon, you just got back, and you're already teasing
me? We're having a serious conversation here.
...Wait. Zeta, do you know about bunny suits?

Hm? Sure. They're casino uniforms, although I've also
seen them in some of the more high-end bars.
See, Epsilon? Do you believe me now?

Tsk. If Zeta, who just arrived, says so, then it must
be true. Fine, I'll believe you.

A-Alright then, here's another question. What exactly
does a bunny girl do?

You should at least know the details of the job
you're infiltrating... Isn't that right, Lady Alpha?
...Yes, that's right.
Well...

Judging by your reaction...you're not saying you
don't know already, are you?
Ack...

Based on the job criteria of customer service skills,
good health, good looks, and the ability to handle
and make decisions in a pinch, plus, given it's a
venue where important individuals gather...

The required skills are considerably high! Putting
all that together, my guess is that the job of a
bunny girl is...
Hey, what in the world are you muttering—
...B-Being a special agent!
...Huh?

At first glance, she's just a bunny girl with silver
hair, blue eyes, a beauty mark beneath her eye,
and excellent customer service...

But her true identity is that of a special agent hired to
protect the customers! She lurks where the aristocrats
gather, secretly guarding dignitaries.

That's a bunny girl's true job, which they can't
mention directly in the advert! Sound good?

What do you mean, "Sound good"?! You just came up
with that, didn't you? It's so obvious! Just admit it, if you
don't know...!

Now, now, calm down, you two... Beta's description of
the job is actually pretty accurate.

Rabbit therianthropes are considered beautiful and
rather cunning amongst the hybrid beasts. If they
based bunny girls on them, it's a possible
explanation.

I see, so it's a costume mimicking the rabbit
therianthropes!

But they're also known for letting their superiority
get to their head, causing them to often slack off.
They say a hare once lost a race against a tortoise,
you know?
Slack off?! Never! I would never slack off!

Well, I'm sure you'll do your research from now, but
just don't let your guard down, okay?

Ooh...I totally know what you mean, Zeta. She tends
to take things for granted, being the airhead she is.

Meanwhile, I'll work hard and steadily build up
results... That's right! I'll win in the end!
What're you talking about...?

*Ahem* Sorry to interrupt the fun, but we're still in
the middle of a meeting. I'll explain the duties and
responsibilities.
You know what they are, Gamma...?

Yes. I learned about bunny girls when our clothing
division was asked to make their uniforms. They're
waitresses of sorts.

They handle various jobs, such as carrying drinks and
chatting with customers, but it seems they primarily
walk around, ensuring customers feel welcome and
comfortable. That's the job of a bunny girl.

It may sound easy enough, but casino clientele is
amongst the highest in the hospitality industry.
They require considerable attention and the best
hospitality, so be sure to exercise caution.
Hmm... Think you can be that attentive, Beta?
E-Excuse me?! Of course I can!
Lady Alpha! Would you let me handle this mission?

...Well, that was always the plan, and I don't intend
to go back on it now.

But don't get ahead of yourself. Gamma has taught you
customer service skills, but so long as we don't know
what to expect, you'll need to study everything from
casino etiquette to game rules.

This is you we're talking about, Beta, so I'm not too
worried, but please be sure to prepare thoroughly.
Yes, of course. Leave it to me!
